    Class representing a non-master mkv element, that contains actual data in an mkv stream. It includes the bytes containing the id and size of the element, the size of the data in the element. When first vended by a StreamingMkvReader it also includes the raw bytes of the data element in the dataBuffer. However, the data buffer can only be accessed before nextIfAvailable is called again on the StreamingMkvReader. To retain the value of the MkvDataElement for later use call getValueCopy() on it. It copies the raw bytes and interprets it based on the type of the MkvDataElement.
